            <title>[OAK-3325] MissingIndexProviderStrategy should warn when setting the reindex flag</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3325</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently the &lt;em&gt;MissingIndexProviderStrategy&lt;/em&gt; would silently flip the reindex flag on missing provider types. We need to add some warning logs to know when this happens for the synchronous indexes too.&lt;/p&gt;




